objecttypes.name: Wellbore
objecttypes.description: A hole in the ground extending from a point at the earth's surface to the maximum point of penetration.

objecttypes.name: GeologicalFormation
objecttypes.description: The name given to a body of rock having a consistent set of physical (litho-stratigraphic), temporal (chrono-stratigraphic) or fossil (bio-stratigraphic) characteristics that distinguishes it from adjacent bodies of rock, and which occupies a particular position in the layers of rock in a geographical region.

objecttypes.name: Well
objecttypes.description: The origin of a set of wellbores.

objecttypes.name: WellFluidDirection
objecttypes.description: Fluid Direction [Well Fluid Direction] is the flow direction of the wellhead stream. The facet value can change over the life of the well.

objecttypes.name: WellProductType
objecttypes.description: Product Type [Well Product Type] is the physical product(s) that can be attributed to any well component.

objecttypes.name: WellboreReason
objecttypes.description: A general description of the technical or operational reason for drilling a wellbore.

objecttypes.name: WellboreTrajectory
objecttypes.description: Work Product Component describing an individual instance of a wellbore trajectory data object. Also called a deviation survey, wellbore trajectory is data that is used to calculate the position and spatial uncertainty of a planned or actual wellbore in 2-dimensional and 3-dimensional space.

objecttypes.name: Coring
objecttypes.description: The activity of acquiring a core from within a wellbore. The two predominant types are by drilling, or by sidewall. In drilling a cylindrical sample of rock is collected using a core bit in conjunction with a core barrel and core catcher. Sidewall cores are taken from the side of the borehole, usually by a wireline tool. Sidewall cores may be taken using percussion or mechanical drilling.

objecttypes.name: HoleSection
objecttypes.description: A section of a wellbore drilled with a constant bit and/or under-reamer diameter

objecttypes.name: OperationsReport
objecttypes.description: A standard report of all drilling, completion or well work events conducted on a well during a given period, usually a 24-hour day, not necessarily aligned with the local time zone. Printed snapshots, e.g. PDF files, are captured as work-product-component--Document, which relate via data.LineageAssertions.

objecttypes.name: RockSample
objecttypes.description: A rock sample retrieved from an outcrop or Well.  It can be core, sample cut from core, cutting, outcrop, slide etc.

objecttypes.name: RockSampleAnalysis
objecttypes.description: The meta-data about a rock sample analysis related to core or outcrop rock samples.

objecttypes.name: SurveyProgram
objecttypes.description: The plan for obtaining directional survey data by survey sections, acquired during a drilling campaign or later post-drilling work.

objecttypes.name: WellboreIntervalSet
objecttypes.description: Define the geologic unit (including stratigraphic units) or fluid intervals along the wellbore, independent or based on markers  (defined in one or several WellboreMarkerSets).

objecttypes.name: WellboreMarkerSet
objecttypes.description: Wellbore Markers identify the depth in a wellbore, measured below a reference elevation, at which a person or an automated process identifies a noteworthy observation, which is usually a change in the rock that intersects that wellbore. Formation Marker data includes attributes/properties that put these depths in context. Formation Markers are sometimes known as picks or formation tops.

objecttypes.name: FormationIntegrityTest
objecttypes.description: A downhole pressure test performed in open hole to measure formation strength.

objecttypes.name: RockImage
objecttypes.description: An image taken of a rock sample such as a core, sidewall core or thin section slide. An image could be a photograph, scan, etc representing a visual representation of the rock sample.

objecttypes.name: WellLog
objecttypes.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

objecttypes.name: WellStatusSummary
objecttypes.description: Identifies the status of a well component in a way that may combine and-or summarize concepts found in other status facets. For example, a Well Status Summary of Gas Injector Shut-in, which contains commonly desired business information, combines concepts from Product Type, Fluid Direction, and Condition.

objecttypes.name: WellRole
objecttypes.description: Role [Well Role] is the current purpose, whether planned or actual. If there are multiple Roles among a wells components, the well may be assigned the facet value with the highest significance. The value of Role may change over the Life Cycle.

objecttypes.name: DrillingReasonType
objecttypes.description: Used to describe the type of drilling reasons.

objecttypes.name: WellboreTrajectoryType
objecttypes.description: Profile Type [Well Profile Type, Wellbore Trajectory Type] is the general geometry of the wellbore relative to the vertical plane. The specific criteria may vary by operator or regulator. The facet value may change if conditions encountered during drilling are not what was planned or permitted.

objecttypes.name: SystemProperties
objecttypes.description: System properties to be injected at root level by the OsduSchemaComposer script.

relshiptypes.name: hasWellbore
relshiptypes.description: This is a pointer to the parent wellbore. The wellbore that starts from top has no parent.

relshiptypes.name: hasGeologicalFormation
relshiptypes.description: The Formation of interest for which the Wellbore is drilled to interact with. The Wellbore may terminate in a lower formation if the requirement is to drill through the entirety of the target formation, therefore this is not necessarily the Formation at TD.

relshiptypes.name: hasWellFluidDirection
relshiptypes.description: Fluid Direction [Well Fluid Direction] is the flow direction of the wellhead stream. The facet value can change over the life of the wellbore.

relshiptypes.name: hasWellProductType
relshiptypes.description: Product Type [Well Product Type] is the physical product(s) that can be attributed to any wellbore component. A Primary Product Significance identifies the Product Type that is most significant.

relshiptypes.name: hasWellboreReason
relshiptypes.description: The relationship to a reference-data record explaining the reason why this wellbore was drilled.

relshiptypes.name: hasWellboreTrajectory
relshiptypes.description: SRN of Wellbore Trajectory which is considered the authoritative or preferred version.

objects.name: Seismic3DInterpretationSet
objects.description: A seismic 3D interpretation survey is a collection of trace datasets with a common bin grid that are important for interpretation.  It does not comprise all of the datasets with a common bin grid, nor all of the datasets from a processing project, nor all of the datasets from an acquisition project, because some are not suitable for interpretation.  An interpretation survey may include datasets from more than one acquisition or processing project.  Consequently, it is not an acquisition survey nor a processing survey.  It is not an application project, which is a collection of all the various objects an application and user care about for some analysis (seismic, wells, etc.).  It inherits properties shared by project entities because it can serve to capture the archiving of a master or authorized project activity. Interpretation objects (horizons) are hung from an interpretation survey to give context and to derive spatial location based on the common bin grid.  Trace datasets and seismic horizons are associated through LineageAssertion, although a master collection of trace datasets and horizons are explicitly related through a child relationship property.

objects.name: GeologicUnitOccurrenceInterpretation
objects.description:
Interpretation of a sequence of geologic units actually observed (interpreted)  along or inside a representation, the representation can be 
	1D such as a well or an arbitrary line
	2D like a cross section
	3D like a entire model or a group of fault blocks
It is typically based on a stratigraphic column rank but can include more units (example intrusive bodies), duplicated units (repeated sequence along a well or lines), or less units (Eroded or non-deposited).
An ordering criteria indicates the reason for the order (age, apparent depth or measured depth).

objects.name: Seismic2DInterpretationSet
objects.description: A seismic 2D interpretation set is a collection of logical processed lines and associated trace datasets that represent an important and uniform set for interpretation.  It does not comprise all of the datasets with a common processing geometry, nor all of the lines/datasets from a processing project, nor all of the lines/datasets from an acquisition project, because some are not suitable for interpretation.  An interpretation survey may include 2D lines and datasets from more than one acquisition or processing project.  Consequently, it is not an acquisition survey nor a processing survey.  It is not an application project, which is a collection of all the various objects an application and user care about for some analysis (seismic, wells, etc.).  It inherits properties shared by project entities because it can serve to capture the archiving of a master or authorized project activity.  Interpretation objects (horizons) are hung from an interpretation project to give context and to derive spatial location based on the processing geometry of the associated 2D lines. Trace datasets and seismic horizons are associated through LineageAssertion, although a master collection of trace datasets and horizons are explicitly related through a child relationship property.

objects.name: ChronoStratigraphy
objects.description: The reference value type for Chronostratigraphic classification. The purpose of chronostratigraphic classification is to organize systematically the rocks forming the Earth's crust into named units (chronostratigraphic units) that represent intervals of geologic time (geochronologic units) to serve as references in narratives about Earth history including the evolution of life. Records of this kind represent chronostratigraphic units, i.e., bodies of rocks that include all rocks representative of a specific interval of geologic time, and only this time span. Chronostratigraphic units are bounded by isochronous horizons which mark specific moments of geological time. The rank (via data.ChronostratigraphicHierarchy) and relative magnitude of the units in the chronostratigraphic hierarchy are a function of the durations they represent.

objects.description: This is a pointer to the parent wellbore. The wellbore that starts from top has no parent.

objects.name: hasWellboreTrajectoryType
objects.description: Profile Type [Wellbore Trajectory Type] is the general geometry of the wellbore relative to the vertical plane. The specific criteria for Profile Type may vary by operator or regulator. The facet value may change if conditions encountered during drilling are not what was planned or permitted.

objects.name: hasWellboreTrajectory
objects.description: SRN of Wellbore Trajectory which is considered the authoritative or preferred version.

objects.name: hasGeologicalFormation
objects.description: The Formation of interest for which the Wellbore is drilled to interact with. The Wellbore may terminate in a lower formation if the requirement is to drill through the entirety of the target formation, therefore this is not necessarily the Formation at TD.

objects.name: FormationNameAtTotalDepth
objects.description: The name of the formation encountered at total depth. The value is not controlled by any reference value list.

objects.name: DefaultVerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The default datum reference point, or zero depth point, used to determine other points vertically in a wellbore.  References an entry in the Vertical Measurements array of this wellbore.

objects.name: hasWellBusinessIntention
objects.description: Business Intention [Well Business Intention] is the general purpose for which resources are approved for drilling a new well or subsequent wellbore(s).

objects.name: hasWellRole
objects.description: Role [Well Role] is the current purpose, whether planned or actual. If there are multiple Roles among a wellbore's components, the well may be assigned the facet value with the highest significance. The value of Role may change over the Life Cycle.

objects.name: hasWellInterestType
objects.description: Business Interest [Well Interest Type] describes whether a company currently considers a wellbore entity or its data to be a real or planned asset, and if so, the nature of and motivation for that company's interest.

objects.name: WasBusinessInterestFinancialOperated
objects.description: Identifies, for the purpose of current use, if the Business Interest [Well Interest Type] for this Well has ever been FinancialOperated in the past.

objects.name: WasBusinessInterestFinancialNonOperated

objects.name: WasBusinessInterestObligatory
objects.description: Identifies, for the purpose of current use, if the Business Interest [Well Interest Type] for this Well has ever been Obligatory in the past.

objects.name: WasBusinessInterestTechnical
objects.description: Identifies, for the purpose of current use, if the Business Interest [Well Interest Type] for this Well has ever been Technical in the past.

objects.name: hasWellProductType
objects.description: Product Type [Well Product Type] is the physical product(s) that can be attributed to any wellbore component. A Primary Product Significance identifies the Product Type that is most significant.

objects.name: hasWellProductType
objects.description: Product Type [Well Product Type] is the physical product(s) that can be attributed to any wellbore component. A Secondary Product Significance identifies the Product Type that is the second most significant.

objects.name: hasWellProductType

objects.name: hasWellCondition
objects.description: Condition [Well Condition] is the operational state of a wellbore component relative to the Role [Well Role].

objects.description: Fluid Direction [Well Fluid Direction] is the flow direction of the wellhead stream. The facet value can change over the life of the wellbore.

objects.name: hasWellBusinessIntentionOutcome
objects.description: Outcome [Well Drilling Outcome] is the result of attempting to accomplish the Business Intention [Well Business Intention].

relships.description: Reference to Seismic Line Geometry for 2D seismic processing which describes the node positions of the processed bin centers.  These are indexed from the trace file using CMP (not trace number).

relships.description: For most datasets, the acquisition project that generated the underlying field data.  For merges, probably absent (see processing project for set of acquisition projects used in processing this dataset).

relships.description: The processing project from which this trace dataset was produced.  Absent for field data.

relships.name: hasSeismic3DInterpretationSet
relships.description: For a 3D volume (including linear subsets), the id of the Seismic3DInterpretationSet which can be considered the master for the area and of which this trace dataset is a privileged member.  It defines the set of trace datasets of a particular bin grid that form the best set for interpretation (not an acquisition survey).

relships.name: hasSeismic2DInterpretationSet
relships.description: For a 2D line section, SRN of the Seismic2DInterpretationSet which can be considered the master for the area and of which this trace dataset is a privileged member.  It defines the set of trace datasets of a particular cohesive set of 2D processing geometries in a survey area that form the best set for interpretation (not an acquisition survey).

relships.name: hasSeismicBinGrid
relships.description: For 3D projects, BinGridID relates to the primary bin grid geometry for the processing; for 3D merge projects, it relates to the final (re-)projection and re-binning geometry.

relships.name: hasSeismic3DInterpretationSet
relships.description: For picks on 3D datasets, reference to the 3D interpretation set (not the application project nor an acquisition survey) that supported this interpretation.  The seismic geometry (bin grid) needed to interpret the location references is inferred through the interpretation survey and no longer explicitly through this object.  The WPC SpatialArea may reflect the survey area that has the horizon picked on it for shallow search purposes.  Only this or Seismic2DInterpretationSetID may be used, but not both.

relships.name: hasSeismic2DInterpretationSet
relships.description: For picks on 2D datasets, reference to the 2D interpretation set (not the application project nor an acquisition survey) that supported this interpretation.  The seismic geometries (seismic line geometries) needed to interpret the location references are inferred through the interpretation survey.  The WPC SpatialArea may reflect the lines that have the horizon picked on it for shallow search purposes.  Only this or Seismic3DInterpretationSetID may be used, but not both.

relships.name: Bin Grid ID
relships.description: The explicit bin grid geometry for this horizon overriding the geometry defined by the parent Seismic3DInterpretationSet. If empty and Seismic3DInterpretationSetID is populated, the Seismic3DInterpretationSet.SeismicBinGridID applies.

relships.name: hasSeismicLineGeometry
relships.description: Reference to a 2D processing geometry associated with a particular seismic line used in interpretation.  Multiple datasets may refer to this geometry and support the interpretation.

relships.name: hasNotionalSeismicLine
relships.description: SRN reference to the Line concept that comprises all the 2D geometries belonging to the same seismic transect, of which this one is a part.

relships.name: hasSeismic2DInterpretationSet
relships.description: Reference to the Seismic2DInterpretationSet which collects the favored geometries in an area or interpretation set.

relshipviews.description: For 3D projects, BinGridID relates to the primary bin grid geometry for the processing; for 3D merge projects, it relates to the final (re-)projection and re-binning geometry.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismicAcquisitionSurvey
relshipviews.description: If populated, this survey is part of a time-lapse survey sequence. It identifies the preceding SeismicAcquisitionSurvey. The first survey in the sequence has an empty or absent PrecedingTimeLapseSurveyID.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismicBinGrid
relshipviews.description: A reference to the Bin Grid that all the associated traces and horizons are based on.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismicBinGrid
relshipviews.description: Reference to the WPC which describes the node positions of the processed bin centers.  These are indexed from the trace file using inline and crossline.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismicLineGeometry
relshipviews.description: Reference to Seismic Line Geometry for 2D seismic processing which describes the node positions of the processed bin centers.  These are indexed from the trace file using CMP (not trace number).

relshipviews.name: hasSeismicAcquisitionSurvey
relshipviews.description: For most datasets, the acquisition project that generated the underlying field data.  For merges, probably absent (see processing project for set of acquisition projects used in processing this dataset).

relshipviews.name: hasSeismicProcessingProject
relshipviews.description: The processing project from which this trace dataset was produced.  Absent for field data.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismic3DInterpretationSet
relshipviews.description: For a 3D volume (including linear subsets), the id of the Seismic3DInterpretationSet which can be considered the master for the area and of which this trace dataset is a privileged member.  It defines the set of trace datasets of a particular bin grid that form the best set for interpretation (not an acquisition survey).

relshipviews.name: hasSeismic2DInterpretationSet
relshipviews.description: For a 2D line section, SRN of the Seismic2DInterpretationSet which can be considered the master for the area and of which this trace dataset is a privileged member.  It defines the set of trace datasets of a particular cohesive set of 2D processing geometries in a survey area that form the best set for interpretation (not an acquisition survey).

relshipviews.name: hasNotionalSeismicLine
relshipviews.description: SRN reference to the Line concept that comprises all the 2D geometries belonging to the same seismic transect, of which this one is a part.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismic2DInterpretationSet
relshipviews.description: Reference to the Seismic2DInterpretationSet which collects the favored geometries in an area or interpretation set.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismic3DInterpretationSet
relshipviews.description: For picks on 3D datasets, reference to the 3D interpretation set (not the application project nor an acquisition survey) that supported this interpretation.  The seismic geometry (bin grid) needed to interpret the location references is inferred through the interpretation survey and no longer explicitly through this object.  The WPC SpatialArea may reflect the survey area that has the horizon picked on it for shallow search purposes.  Only this or Seismic2DInterpretationSetID may be used, but not both.

relshipviews.name: hasSeismic2DInterpretationSet
relshipviews.description: For picks on 2D datasets, reference to the 2D interpretation set (not the application project nor an acquisition survey) that supported this interpretation.  The seismic geometries (seismic line geometries) needed to interpret the location references are inferred through the interpretation survey.  The WPC SpatialArea may reflect the lines that have the horizon picked on it for shallow search purposes.  Only this or Seismic3DInterpretationSetID may be used, but not both.

relshipviews.name: Bin Grid ID
relshipviews.description: The explicit bin grid geometry for this horizon overriding the geometry defined by the parent Seismic3DInterpretationSet. If empty and Seismic3DInterpretationSetID is populated, the Seismic3DInterpretationSet.SeismicBinGridID applies.

relshipviews.name: Principal Acquisition Project ID
relshipviews.description: For most datasets, the acquisition project that generated the underlying field data.  For merges, probably absent (see processing project for set of acquisition projects used in processing this dataset).

objects.name: WellLog
objects.typeDescription: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.
